./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/Basic.html#WickContraction.congrLift\">congrLift</a> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/InsertAndContractNat.html#WickContraction.insertLift\">insertLift</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a>   <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fin/SuccPred.html#finCongr\">finCongr</a> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">i</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fin/SuccPred.html#Fin.succAbove\">succAbove</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φsΛ</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/Basic.html#WickContraction.fstFieldOfContract\">fstFieldOfContract</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/InsertAndContract.html#WickContraction.insertAndContract_fstFieldOfContract","kind":"theorem","line":51,"name":"WickContraction.insertAndContract_fstFieldOfContract","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L51-L57"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/InsertAndContract.html#WickContraction.«term_↩Λ___»\"><span class=\"name\">WickContraction</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_↩Λ___»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a Wick contraction `φsΛ` for a list `φs` of `𝓕.FieldOp`,\nan element `φ` of `𝓕.FieldOp`, an `i ≤ φs.length` and a `k`\nin `Option φsΛ.uncontracted` i.e. is either `none` or\nsome element of `φsΛ.uncontracted`, the new Wick contraction\n`φsΛ.insertAndContract φ i k` is defined by inserting `φ` into `φs` after\nthe first `i`-elements and moving the values representing the contracted pairs in `φsΛ`\naccordingly.\nIf `k` is not `none`, but rather `some k`, to this contraction is added the contraction\nof `φ` (at position `i`) with the new position of `k` after `φ` is added.\n\nIn other words, `φsΛ.insertAndContract φ i k` is formed by adding `φ` to `φs` at position `i`,\nand contracting `φ` with the field originally at position `k` if `k` is not `none`.\nIt is a Wick contraction of the list `φs.insertIdx φ i` corresponding to `φs` with `φ` inserted at\nposition `i`.\n\nThe notation `φsΛ ↩Λ φ i k` is used to denote `φsΛ.insertAndContract φ i k`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/InsertAndContract.html#WickContraction.«term_↩Λ___»","kind":"def","line":48,"name":"WickContraction.«term_↩Λ___»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L48-L49"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/InsertAndContract.html#WickContraction.insertAndContract\"><span class=\"name\">WickContraction</span>.<span class=\"name\">insertAndContract</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">φs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">φsΛ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/Basic.html#WickContraction\">WickContraction</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φs</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.length\">length</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φs</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.length\">length</a></span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat.succ\">succ</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φsΛ</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/Uncontracted.html#WickContraction.uncontracted\">uncontracted</a></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/Basic.html#WickContraction\">WickContraction</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">φs</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.insertIdx\">insertIdx</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.length\">length</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a Wick contraction `φsΛ` for a list `φs` of `𝓕.FieldOp`,\nan element `φ` of `𝓕.FieldOp`, an `i ≤ φs.length` and a `k`\nin `Option φsΛ.uncontracted` i.e. is either `none` or\nsome element of `φsΛ.uncontracted`, the new Wick contraction\n`φsΛ.insertAndContract φ i k` is defined by inserting `φ` into `φs` after\nthe first `i`-elements and moving the values representing the contracted pairs in `φsΛ`\naccordingly.\nIf `k` is not `none`, but rather `some k`, to this contraction is added the contraction\nof `φ` (at position `i`) with the new position of `k` after `φ` is added.\n\nIn other words, `φsΛ.insertAndContract φ i k` is formed by adding `φ` to `φs` at position `i`,\nand contracting `φ` with the field originally at position `k` if `k` is not `none`.\nIt is a Wick contraction of the list `φs.insertIdx φ i` corresponding to `φs` with `φ` inserted at\nposition `i`.\n\nThe notation `φsΛ ↩Λ φ i k` is used to denote `φsΛ.insertAndContract φ i k`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/WickContraction/InsertAndContract.html#WickContraction.insertAndContract","kind":"def","line":27,"name":"WickContraction.insertAndContract","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L27-L46"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.WickContraction.UncontractedList"],"instances":[],"name":"PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.WickContraction.InsertAndContract"}